article.headline: Missouri State 87, Drake 82
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Tyler Chaney scored a team-high 20 points, including six in overtime, to lead Missouri State past Drake 87-82 Wednesday night. Chaney drilled a three-pointer with 3:59 left in overtime then made a three-point play with 1:07 to put the Bears (16-7, 7-5) up for good at 82-80. Missouri State made five straight free throws down the stretch to seal the win. Drake (12-11, 3-9) had built a 16-point lead when Klayton Korver, who finished with 19 points, was fouled on a three-point shot and made all three free throws to make it 59-43 with 13:09 left. The Bears kept chipping away at the lead, though, and used a 10-point run at the end the game to tie it at 74 all. Ajay Calvin led the Bulldogs with 22 points and Nick Grant added 20. Blake Ahearn and Dale Lamberth each had 12 points for the Bears.
